comment: Dellavedova (CLE) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Rose's (CHI) drive to the basket.
After Noah (CHI) and Thompson (CLE) briefly engage during rebounding, Noah makes contact with Thompson's arm, but it does not affect his ability to secure the rebound.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Noah (CHI) was overturned and Chicago was awarded possession.
Noah (CHI) moves his pivot foot heel to toe to create space.
Dunleavy (CHI) and Shumpert (CLE) briefly engage away from the ball.
James (CLE) does not go through Dunleavy's (CHI) space.
Dellavedova (CLE) makes incidental contact with Rose (CHI) that does not affect his movement to the basket or shot attempt.
Noah (CHI) sets the screen on James (CLE) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Thompson (CLE) and Noah (CHI) briefly engage during rebounding.
Dunleavy (CHI) commits a take foul on Irving (CLE).
James (CLE) does not affect Butler's (CHI) ability to catch the pass.
Hinrich (CHI) commits a take foul on James (CLE).
Noah (CHI) begins his screen on Dellavedova (CLE) while his right foot is out of bounds.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials determined that the clock continued to run after the foul was committed by Mirotic (CHI). The game clock was reset to 00:02.
Mirotic (CHI) commits a take foul on Irving (CLE).
